title: PML-N’s Tanvir Aslam Malik wins PP-21 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Tanvir Aslam Malik of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-21 Chakwal-II by securing 83,055 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Tariq Mehmood Afzal, who bagged 75,142 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 58.75 %.
